headline: Mid-Cap Index Funds Aren’t All Alike. Look Under the Hood.
summary: Index-fund investors aren’t supposed to worry about picking individual stocks, but when it comes to those tracking mid-cap companies, it isn’t that simple.  Among the most popular mid-cap exchange-traded funds, those benefiting from bets on a few hot tech and crypto-adjacent stocks such as  Palantir Technologies Robinhood  and  Coinbase  have far outperformed at least one prominent fund that doesn’t, according to a new report by CFRA.  The discrepancy highlights how seemingly small differences in index methodology can translate into significant results for investors.
